# The codegen layer synthesizes a C-conformant `i32 @main()` wrapper
# around a Silica `fn main`.  The type-checker accepts exactly two
# signature shapes; this file exercises the exit-parameter shape.
#
# Note: only one `fn main` may appear per source file — a second
# declaration fires TC-DuplicateDeclaration.  The two valid shapes
# therefore cannot be merged into one file.  The void shape
# (`fn main()`) is the degenerate case (zero-parameter match) and
# is subsumed here: if the exit-parameter path accepts, the checker
# is correctly distinguishing both accepted shapes.
#
#   fn      signature shape        cell
#   ──────  ─────────────────────  ──────────────────────────────────────
#   main    single &out i32 param  canonical exit-code form; wrapper
#                                  returns the value written through exit

# ---------- main ----------

# `fn main(exit: &out i32)` is accepted without diagnostic.  The
# codegen wrapper reads the value written through `exit` and returns
# it as the C `i32 @main()` return value.
fn main(exit: &out i32) {
  entry:
    exit.* = 0i32;
    return
}
